    <h2>5.3 Active vs Passive Investing</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Active Investing</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Pursues Alpha (outperform the market).</li>
                <li>Advantages: If you pick right, can significantly outperform the market.</li>
                <li>Disadvantages: Extremely difficult, most people underperform the market.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Passive Investing</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Follows Beta (market average returns).</li>
                <li>Advantages: Stable, time-saving, low fees.</li>
                <li>Disadvantages: Won't get "excess returns", only enjoy market average.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    
